com.nokia.dempsy.container
Class MpContainer

java.lang.Object
  com.nokia.dempsy.container.MpContainer
All Implemented Interfaces:
Listener, OutputInvoker, RoutingStrategy.Inbound.KeyspaceResponsibilityChangeListener
public class MpContainer
extends Object
implements Listener, OutputInvoker, RoutingStrategy.Inbound.KeyspaceResponsibilityChangeListener

The MpContainer manages the lifecycle of message processors for the node that it's instantiated in.

The container is simple in that it does no thread management. When it's called it assumes that the transport has provided the thread that's needed

onMessage

public boolean onMessage(byte[] data,
                         boolean fastfail)

Method that accepts the callback for received messages. Given that the transport is responsible for managing threads, the transport will also let the Listener implementation know if it should make every effort to handle the request or if it should "fail-fast."

fail-fast means that the Listener should not attempt to handle a request if any blocking is required. In cases where the Listener determines there is going to be a delay in processing the request it should simple return 'false' as an indication that the message was not handled and allow the transport implementation to deal with it.

Specified by:
onMessage in interface Listener
Parameters:
data - The message bytes received
Returns:
true, to acknowledge the message.

setConcurrency

public void setConcurrency(int concurrency)
Description copied from interface: OutputInvoker
If the OutputExecuter wants the container to run the Output pass in a multithreaded manner, then calling this method and setting the concurrency to greater than 1 will do that. This method will usually be called once, at initialization. Each time it's called the Executor used by the container will be recreated with all of its attending threads so this method should not be called with each invokeOutput call.

Specified by:
setConcurrency in interface OutputInvoker
Parameters:
concurrency - is the number of threads to allow Output to be run simultaneously.

invokeOutput

public void invokeOutput()
Description copied from interface: OutputInvoker

This method will be called by client application to invoke the @Output methods of MPs. Dempsy will execute the @Output method of all MPs. During the Output execution, MP will not receive any incoming message.

Specified by:
invokeOutput in interface OutputInvoker
